legacy.full_text: These were the earliest #Chinese characters, called 甲骨文 jiǎ gǔ wén (Oracle bone script.) They were engraved on animal bones or turtle plastrons. Oracle bone script was used in the late 2nd millennium BC, and is the earliest known form of Chinese writing. https://t.co/nxKJomDK1E
